<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="67" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,1033,1670]" pageId="17" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1465,1490]" pageId="17" pageNumber="67">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Gressitt, J. L." box="[322,504,1465,1490]" journalOrPublisher="Lingnan Science Journal" pageId="17" pageNumber="67" pagination="161 - 186" part="18" refString="Gressitt, J. L. (1939 a) Hispine beetles in the collection of the Lingnan natural history survey and museum (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae: Cassidinae). Lingnan Science Journal, 18, 161 - 186 + pl. 5." title="Hispine beetles in the collection of the Lingnan natural history survey and museum (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae: Cassidinae)" type="journal article" year="1939" yearSuffix="a">Gressitt (1939a)</bibRefCitation>
described it as a distinct species and compared to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Gestro, 1897)" authorityName="Gestro" authorityYear="1897" baseAuthorityName="Gestro" baseAuthorityYear="1897" box="[1074,1365,1466,1490]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Dactylispa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pugnax">
<emphasis box="[1074,1191,1466,1489]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="67">D. pugnax</emphasis>
(Gestro, 1897)
</taxonomicName>
. Later on, 
<bibRefCitation author="Gressitt, J. L." box="[194,363,1501,1526]" journalOrPublisher="Lingnan Science Journal" pageId="17" pageNumber="67" pagination="53 - 142" part="23" refString="Gressitt, J. L. (1950) The Hispine beetles of China (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae). Lingnan Science Journal, 23, 53 - 142 + pls. 4 - 8." title="The Hispine beetles of China (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae)" type="journal article" year="1950">Gressitt (1950)</bibRefCitation>
downgraded its rank to subspecies of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Uhmann" authorityYear="1927" box="[799,912,1502,1525]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Dactylispa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sauteri">
<emphasis box="[799,912,1502,1525]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="67">D. sauteri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
without any additional comments. 
<bibRefCitation author="Chen, S. &amp; Yu, P. &amp; Sun, C. &amp; Tʼan, C. &amp; Zia, Y." bookContentInfo="653 pp." journalOrPublisher="Science Press, Beijing, xv" pageId="17" pageNumber="67" refString="Chen, S., Yu, P., Sun, C., Tʼan, C. &amp; Zia, Y. (1986) Fauna Sinica. Insecta. Coleoptera Hispidae. Science Press, Beijing, xv + 653 pp. + 15 pls." title="Fauna Sinica. Insecta. Coleoptera Hispidae" type="book" year="1986">
Chen 
<emphasis box="[1379,1436,1501,1526]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="67">et al.</emphasis>
(1986)
</bibRefCitation>
considered the taxon as plain synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Uhmann" authorityYear="1927" box="[709,822,1538,1561]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Dactylispa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sauteri">
<emphasis box="[709,822,1538,1561]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="67">D. sauteri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It differs from typical 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Uhmann" authorityYear="1927" box="[1087,1200,1538,1561]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Dactylispa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sauteri">
<emphasis box="[1087,1200,1538,1561]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="67">D. sauteri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in shorter spines but their position is exactly the same and by presence of indistinct dark brown patches on the apical half of the elytra near the apical margin. These characters are in our opinion fully within variability of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Uhmann" authorityYear="1927" box="[1111,1223,1610,1633]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Dactylispa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sauteri">
<emphasis box="[1111,1223,1610,1633]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="67">D. sauteri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and we agree with the synonymy.
</paragraph>
